Spark creates a DAG representing all the RDDs and how they'll be transformed

- transformations construct the graph, actions trigger computations on it

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Narrow Dependencies**
Each partition of the parent RDD is used by at most 1 partition of the child RDD (injective)
e.g. map, flatmap, filter, contains

**Wide Dependencies**
each partition of parent RDD is used by multiple partitions of the child RDD
e.g. reduceByKey, groupBy, orderBy

Stages

- Consecutive narrow deps grped tgt as stages
- within stages, spark performs consec transformations on same machines
- across stages, data needs to be shuffled
	- data is written to the target worker node's DISK
- to improve performance, need to minimise shuffling
